<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138843" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera lea Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Ponera lea Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lea">Ponera lea Sants</taxonomicName>
. (Rev. Zool. afric, XXX [1937], p. 73).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="79">
— Cette espece est voisine de 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:141651" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera cognata Emery" lsidName-HNS="Ponera cognata Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognata">P. cognata Sants</taxonomicName>
. Elle s'en distingue toutefois par ses mandibules un peu plus courtes, aux 4 e a 5 e dents anterieures plus grandes (denticulees chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:141651" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera cognata Emery" lsidName-HNS="Ponera cognata Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognata">cognata</taxonomicName>
), la tete plus large, l' epistome plus nettement carene, le scape plus court, le tout plus luisant. Dans la figure accompagnant la description de 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138843" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera lea Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Ponera lea Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lea">P. lea</taxonomicName>
, la suture promesonotale de la vue de profil est mal venue, je donne ci-inclus une figure rectificatrice.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
